  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skin on) into <strong>chips</strong></p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>chips</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the <strong>chips</strong> are golden and starting to crisp</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Lato; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap; font-weight: bold;\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>pear<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>into very small pieces, discarding the core</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-2.a-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-2.a-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-2.a-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-2.a-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-2.a-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid over a medium heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> and the<strong> chopped pear</strong> and cook for 3-5 min or until starting to soften</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once starting to soften, add the <strong>sultanas</strong>, <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong>, <strong>star anise</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until the <strong>pear</strong> pieces have broken down &ndash; this is your <strong>pear chutney</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: if the chutney is looking too chunky, mash it roughly with a fork</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-4.a-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-4.a-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-4.a-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-4.a-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-4.a-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, crumble the <strong>blue cheese</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add&nbsp;the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>pork mince </strong>and<strong> crumbled blue cheese&nbsp;</strong>to a large bowl with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: if you don't love blue cheese, just add half!</p>\r\n<p>Mix, then knead thoroughly until fully combined, then shape into 2&nbsp;<span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span>&nbsp;<strong>burger patties </strong>and refrigerate&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1292.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
